<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-669-683  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 669 683.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Nov 19 1990 v24 n47 p111(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Before you burn out, chill out: ward off IS stress by kickingback, accentuating the positive and being a good communicatorwho's open to change.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ryan, Alan J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Many progressive organizations offer their employees programs tohelp deal with job stress as well as side benefits such asphysical fitness centers to counter the rigors of work.andO;Information systems (IS) professionals offer other advice on howto alleviate stress related problems.andP;  One piece of advice is thattechnical people need to develop better communications skills andlearn to network and participate in office politics to theiradvantage.andP;  IS professionals should also be open to change;flexibility is one of the best ways to combat stress.andP;  Settingrealistic deadlines and not overextending yourself or thedepartment will also reduce stress.andP;  Similarly, developing thenotion of teamwork at the workplace will mitigate individualpressure and stress.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MISInformation SystemsManagement StyleStressMethodsTutorial.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>